  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Instructor",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></u></p><ul><li>Teach and conduct coding, STEM and technology-related projects for Pre-School & Primary School students.</li><li>Take up teaching duties if the need arises: Take up teaching duties when needed, including covering regular classes, holidays, and special programs.</li><li>Develop close relationships with students and parents to understand their needs and ensure that the team delivers lessons that are up to expectations.</li><li>Collaborate with other departments: Work collaboratively with other departments to ensure a coordinated approach to teaching and learning across Titan Tech Academy.</li></ul><p><u><strong>SKILLS & QUALIFICATIONS</strong></u></p><ul><li>Preferably a Diploma in an Information Technology, Engineering, Mathematics or Science related field and above.</li><li>Good programming background with a positive learning attitude.</li><li>Should be proficient in using Scratch and Python in teaching and curriculum research.</li><li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.</li><li>Required to work on work on weekends.</li></ul><p><u><strong>What You'll Get</strong></u></p><ul><li>Become our pioneer to grow and expand with us in our cutting-edge AI programmes that deliver unique learning experiences to inspire & stretch the potential of all students, regardless of their ability.</li><li>Structured Career & Salary Progression</li><li>Great & Passionate Colleagues; Vibrant Environment</li></ul>",
